WEBVTT

00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:01.143
but you worry about the details,
about how that's going to happen.

00:03:01.167 --> 00:03:03.143
And that was the message that I absorbed

00:03:03.167 --> 00:03:04.976
when I was in med school.

00:03:05.000 --> 00:03:07.976
I was an obsessive compulsive student.

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:10.976
In high school, a classmate once said

00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:13.286
that Brian Goldman would study
for a blood test.

00:03:13.310 --> 00:03:15.976
(Laughter)

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:17.976
And so I did.

00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:19.976
And I studied in my little garret

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:22.524
at the nurses' residence
at Toronto General Hospital,

00:03:22.548 --> 00:03:23.976
not far from here.

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:25.976
And I memorized everything.

00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:27.976
I memorized in my anatomy class

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:30.000
the origins and exertions of every muscle,